"Dockside follows where the Dock goes, by default (automatic mode).Sometimes the macOS display settings may interfere with this. To properly move the Dock (and the Dockside) to the other screen Navigate to 'System Settings' > 'Displays' > Click on 'Arrange...' and move the white menu bar to the screen you want to set as primary. This will make that display your main display in macOS with Dock in it.\nDockside will automatically move here too and work as expected. To force move the Dockside to one of your screens, select from the below." = "Dockside follows where the Dock goes, by default (automatic mode).Sometimes the macOS display settings may interfere with this. To properly move the Dock (and the Dockside) to the other screen Navigate to 'System Settings' > 'Displays' > Click on 'Arrange...' and move the white menu bar to the screen you want to set as primary. This will make that display your main display in macOS with Dock in it.\nDockside will automatically move here too and work as expected. To force move the Dockside to one of your screens, select from the below.";
"Dockside occasionally shows a few useful tips near the menu bar icon that are relevant from time to time. However, if the menu bar icon is disabled or if you have installed menu bar customization apps (like Bartender or Ice), Dockside will automatically disable the popups to reduce annoyance." = "Dockside occasionally shows a few useful tips near the menu bar icon that are relevant from time to time. However, if the menu bar icon is disabled or if you have installed menu bar customization apps (like Bartender or Ice), Dockside will automatically disable the popups to reduce annoyance.";
